nonsensical manner. The phrase you need
to focus on is 'everybody besides me' (and
possibly 'everybody besides you / him / her
/ us / them'). Such a phrase is only going
to be used in particular circumstances:
i.e. in some kind of personal confession or
accusatory context. So you're unlikely to
find it in the Bible or in a set of essays.

